  "texts": [
    "In the second set of analyses, we evaluated how many relevant studies selected for full-text screening would be identified when using learning algorithms with heuristic stopping criteria (RQ2).",
    "For the first set of analyses, we estimated the specificity and estimated time savings (ETS) at a 95% sensitivity for each learning algorithm across the 27 abstract collections.",
    "For the second set of analyses, we estimated the sensitivity, specificity, and estimated time savings of the time-based, data-driven, and mixed-strategy heuristic stopping criteria across the 27 abstract collections and ten learning algorithms.",
    "The performance metrics were defined as follows: a.",
    "Sensitivity (recall): The proportion of relevant studies in an abstract collection identified by the learning algorithms out of the total deemed relevant by the authors of the systematic review (Howard et al., 2020)."
